            </ul>
        </aside>

        <div class="faq-list">
            <div class="faq-section" id="getting-started">
                <h2>Getting Started</h2>
                <details open>
                    <summary>How do I create an account?</summary>
                    <p>Use the Sign Up button in the top navigation and complete the registration form. Once created, you can place orders and leave reviews.</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>How do I become a seller?</summary>
                    <p>After logging in, select “Become a Seller” from the navigation. Add your business details and you’ll be able to list services.</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>Can I switch between buyer and seller?</summary>
                    <p>Yes. Your account can hold both roles. You can still place orders even after becoming a seller.</p>
                </details>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-section" id="payments">
                <h2>Payments & Orders</h2>
                <details>
                    <summary>When is my card charged?</summary>
                    <p>Payments are collected at checkout. You’ll see a confirmation immediately after your order is placed.</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>Can I cancel an order?</summary>
                    <p>Yes. Navigate to My Orders and choose the order you want to cancel. If the seller has already started, reach out via chat.</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>Where can I track order status?</summary>
                    <p>Order status appears on the order detail page and updates automatically as the seller completes the work.</p>
                </details>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-section" id="reviews">
                <h2>Reviews</h2>
                <details>
                    <summary>When can I leave a review?</summary>
                    <p>Reviews are available once an order is completed. You’ll see a “Leave a Review” button on the order detail page.</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>Who can leave reviews and what is included?</summary>
                    <p>Only buyers with a completed, verified order can submit a review. Each review includes a rating, written comment, optional tags, and a submission date and time.</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>How does TrustMate verify reviews?</summary>
                    <p>Every review is linked to a completed order before it can be submitted. If the order is not completed or verified, the system blocks the review.</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>Can sellers reply to reviews?</summary>
                    <p>Yes. Sellers can post one reply per review on their service detail pages. Replies are shown alongside the original review with a reply timestamp.</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>How do I edit a review?</summary>
                    <p>Open the review from the service or order page and select edit. You can update the rating, comment, and tags.</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>How are reviews displayed publicly?</summary>
                    <p>Reviews appear on the seller’s profile and the related service listing. If a review is under admin review, it may be temporarily hidden from public view.</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>How do admins moderate or remove reviews?</summary>
                    <p>Buyers can report suspicious or inappropriate reviews. Reported reviews are flagged for admin review, and admins can mark them as reviewed, dismissed, or action taken. Admins can hide or remove reviews that violate platform policies, and these actions are logged for transparency.</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>How are disputes and fraud handled?</summary>
                    <p>Review moderation is linked to our fraud reporting system. Admins can investigate flagged reviews and orders to support dispute resolution and protect marketplace trust.</p>
                </details>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-section" id="sellers">
                <h2>Seller Policies</h2>
                <details>
                    <summary>What makes a seller verified?</summary>
                    <p>Verified sellers have completed additional checks and consistently deliver high-quality services.</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>How do I manage my listings?</summary>
                    <p>Visit Seller Dashboard to create, update, or pause services. Keep your descriptions clear and pricing transparent.</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>What happens if I miss a deadline?</summary>
                    <p>Communicate early with the buyer via chat. Consistent delays may impact your seller status.</p>
                </details>
            </div>

            <div class="faq-section" id="support">
                <h2>Support</h2>
                <details>
                    <summary>How do I report an issue?</summary>
                    <p>Contact support through the Help Center or send us a message via chat for urgent matters.</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>What if I suspect fraud?</summary>
                    <p>Flag the order in your account and our team will review it promptly.</p>
                </details>
                <details>
                    <summary>Still need help?</summary>
                    <p>Email us at support@trustmate.com and we’ll get back within 24 hours.</p>
                </details>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

